The indefinite integral of ln(x)/sinh(x) is ln(x)/sinh(x) - sinh(x). Now let's substitute 'x=4' into the result of the indefinite integral:

ln(4)/sinh(4) - sinh(4) = ln(4) - (2.3377 + 8.4576) = ln(4) - 10.7953

The final result is 10. The expression represents the natural logarithm of 4 divided by the hyperbolic sine of 4, minus 10.7953. Please round down to get the integer result: 10.
